.TH LCAL 1 "March 2026" "lcal" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lcal \- a simple terminal calendar with timezone support
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lcal
[\fB\-l\fR]
[\fB\-t\fR \fITIMEZONE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lcal
is a terminal user-interface (TUI) calendar application written in Python.
It displays a monthly calendar grid alongside a sidebar showing a todo list
and the events for the currently selected day.
Events are stored in iCalendar (.ics) format and all timed events carry full
IANA timezone information.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-list\-timezones
Print every available IANA timezone name to standard output and exit.
.TP
.BR \-t " \fITIMEZONE\fR, " \-\-set\-timezone " \fITIMEZONE\fR"
Persist \fITIMEZONE\fR (an IANA zone name such as
.IR Europe/London )
to the configuration file and exit.
.SH KEY BINDINGS
Key bindings can be customised in the configuration file (see
.BR FILES ).
The defaults are listed below.
.SS Global
.TP
.B Tab
Toggle focus between the calendar and the sidebar.
.TP
.B q
Quit the application.
.TP
.B g
Go to a specific date.
.TP
.B z
Change the display timezone interactively.
.SS Calendar view
.TP
.BR h " / " \(la
Move the cursor one day to the left.
.TP
.BR l " / " \(ra
Move the cursor one day to the right.
.TP
.BR j " / " \(da
Move the cursor one week down.
.TP
.BR k " / " \(ua
Move the cursor one week up.
.TP
.B t
Jump the cursor to today's date.
.TP
.B n
Advance to the next month.
.TP
.B p
Go back to the previous month.
.TP
.B a
Add a new event on the currently selected day.
.TP
.B i
Enter event-selection mode for the currently selected day.
.SS Event-selection mode
.TP
.B Esc
Exit event-selection mode.
.TP
.BR j " / " \(da
Move selection to the next event.
.TP
.BR k " / " \(ua
Move selection to the previous event.
.TP
.B e
Edit the selected event (name, start time, end time, colour, or move to a new date).
A sub-prompt offers:
.BR s " (start time), " e " (end time), " n " (name), " c " (colour), " m " (move to date)."
.TP
.B d
Delete the selected event.
.TP
.B n
Open the selected event's description in
.BR $EDITOR .
.SS Sidebar (TODO list)
.TP
.BR j " / " \(da
Move the todo cursor down.
.TP
.BR k " / " \(ua
Move the todo cursor up.
.TP
.B a
Add a new todo item.
.TP
.B e
Edit the selected todo item.
.TP
.B n
Open the selected todo's note file in
.BR $EDITOR .
.TP
.B d
Delete the selected todo item.
.TP
.BR + " / " =
Raise the todo item's priority (towards 1).
.TP
.B \-
Lower the todo item's priority (towards 9).
.SH ADDING EVENTS
Press
.B a
in the calendar view to add an event:
.IP 1. 4
Enter a start time in
.B HH:MM
or
.B HHMM
format (24-hour by default), or press Enter to create an all-day event.
.IP 2.
Enter an end time in the same format, or press Enter to omit.  The end time
must be strictly
.I after
the start time; entering an equal or earlier time is rejected with an error
message.
.IP 3.
Enter the event name.
.IP 4.
Choose an optional colour.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file is
.B ~/.config/lcal/config.py
and is a plain Python script evaluated at startup.  It is created
automatically with defaults on the first run.
.SS Configuration keys
.TP
.B ics_path
Path to the primary iCalendar file.
.TP
.B timezone
IANA timezone name used for displaying and entering timed events.
.TP
.B show_timezone
Boolean.  Display the timezone abbreviation in the calendar header.
.TP
.B show_day_borders
Boolean.  Draw borders between calendar cells.
.TP
.B first_weekday
Integer 1–7.  First day of the week (1=Monday, 7=Sunday).
.TP
.B sidebar_ratio
Float 0–1.  Fraction of the terminal width occupied by the sidebar.
.TP
.B notes_extension
File extension for event descriptions and todo notes (default
.IR md ).
.TP
.B show_events_tab
Boolean.  Show the Events section in the sidebar.
.TP
.B holidays_ics_path
Path to a read-only iCalendar file containing public holidays.
.TP
.B holiday_colour
Curses colour name used to highlight holiday dates
(e.g.\&
.IR COLOR_RED ).
.TP
.B time_24h
Boolean.
.B True
for 24-hour clock (14:30),
.B False
for 12-hour AM/PM display (02:30PM).
.TP
.B date_format
Format used when entering dates in the "go to date" prompt.
Accepted values:
.BR dd/mm/yyyy ,
.BR mm/dd/yyyy ,
.BR yyyy/mm/dd ,
.BR yyyy-mm-dd .
.TP
.B event_date_format
A
.BR strftime (3)
format string controlling the date label shown in the Events sidebar.
For example
.B %a %d %b %Y
produces
.IR "Mon 01 Jan 2024" .
.TP
.B editor
Editor command used to open event descriptions and todo notes (e.g.\&
.IR nano ,
.IR nvim ,
.IR micro ).
Falls back to the
.B EDITOR
environment variable and then
.IR vim .
.TP
.B event_spacing
Boolean.  When
.B True
(the default), a blank spacer line is drawn between the day number and the
first event, and between consecutive events within a day cell.  Set to
.B False
to pack events tightly.
.TP
.B events_tab_ratio
Float 0–1.  Fraction of the sidebar height occupied by the Events tab
(default 0.5).  Increase to give more space to events; decrease to give more
space to the TODO list.
.TP
.B day_names
List of seven strings, starting from Monday, used as column headers.
.TP
.B month_names
List of twelve month name strings.
.TP
.B colours
Dictionary mapping UI element names to
.I [foreground, background]
curses colour pairs.  Element names:
.BR cursor ,
.BR header ,
.BR weekend ,
.BR today ,
.BR accent .
.TP
.B keybindings
Dictionary mapping action names to single-character strings.  Only the
actions you wish to override need to be present; unspecified actions keep
their defaults.  Available action names:
.BR quit ,
.BR goto_date ,
.BR change_timezone ,
.BR go_today ,
.BR next_month ,
.BR prev_month ,
.BR add_event ,
.BR enter_event_selection ,
.BR edit_event ,
.BR delete_event ,
.BR edit_description ,
.BR move_up ,
.BR move_down ,
.BR move_left ,
.BR move_right ,
.BR todo_add ,
.BR todo_edit ,
.BR todo_open ,
.BR todo_delete ,
.BR todo_priority_up ,
.BR todo_priority_down .
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/lcal/config.py
User configuration file.
.TP
.B ~/.config/lcal/calendar.ics
Primary event store in iCalendar format.
.TP
.B ~/.config/lcal/holidays.ics
Optional read-only holiday calendar.
.TP
.B ~/.config/lcal/todo/
Directory containing todo item files.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B EDITOR
Editor launched when opening event descriptions or todo notes.
The
.B editor
configuration key takes precedence when set; this variable is consulted
as a fallback, and
.I vim
is used when neither is set.
.TP
.B ESCDELAY
Milliseconds to wait after receiving ESC before treating it as a standalone
key.  lcal sets this to
.B 25
ms unless already defined in the environment.
